./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:"zItemSubDEF.RecID"
./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:"SELECT zPromo.RecID, zPromo.ID, zVendor.Company, zVendor.VendorCode, zPromo.Prom"
./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:"oNm, zPromo.PromoOffer, zPromo.OfferText, zPromo.EffDate, zPromo.ExpDate, zPromo"
./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:".MediaMn, zPromo.EffMnth, zPromo.EffQtr, zPromo.EffYr, zItemSub.HSICode, zItemSu"
./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:"b.VIC, zItemSub.VndCd, zItemSub.ProdNm, zItemSub.ProdDesc FROM (zPromo LEFT JOIN"
./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:" zVendor ON zPromo.ID = zVendor.ID) RIGHT JOIN zItemSub ON zPromo.RecID = zItemS"
./forms/zItemSubDEF.bas:"ub.RecID ORDER BY zVendor.Company;"

./forms/zPromoSubSelRecF.bas:"uite, zPromo.CityStZip, zPromo.VndTel, zPromo.VndFax, zPromo.WebSite, zPromo.Pro"

./forms/zPromoSubSelRecF.bas:"mo.BuyCnt, zPromo.[1inv], zPromo.DftNote, zPromo.Comment, zPromo.Same, zPromo.Br"
./forms/zPromoSubSelRecF.bas:"andNmPkg, zPromo.ImpDt, IIf(([DefPro].[DftPromo])=-1,\"D\",Null) AS DftSub, DefP"
./forms/zPromoSubSelRecF.bas:"ro.DftD, zPromo.Limit, zPromo.DivPrc FROM zPromo LEFT JOIN DefPro ON zPromo.RecI"
./forms/zPromoSubSelRecF.bas:"D = DefPro.RecID WHERE (((zPromo.EffQtr)=ZEffQtr()) AND ((zPromo.EffYr)=ZEffYr()"

./forms/zPromoSubSelRecF.bas:"fYr()) AND ((ZPer())=\"M\")) ORDER BY zPromo.PromoNm, zPromo.ExpDate, zPromo.Med"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"Kill Dups -  Created 1/13/2010"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"Strategy - Determine first instance of all [zPromo] records. Create table of [zP"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"romo].[RecID] Dups."
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"                  Use Dups table [zPromoDupsT] to delete dup records in [zBuy] a"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"nd [zItemSub]."
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"                  Clean out any [zItemSub] \"Sub-Dups\" (a Good [RecID] but cont"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"aining duped ItemCodes)."
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"Tactics - "
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     1. Create a Table of [zPromo] Dups by [RecID]             "
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     2. Delete Dups in [zPromo]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     3. Use table [zPromoDupsT] to delete orphaned [zBuys]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     4. Use table [zPromoDupsT] to delete orphaned [zItemSubs]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     5. Kill duped ItemCodes in [zItemSub] - Good Promos but ItemCodes duped"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"***** StopMacro keeps us from accidentally running this process *****"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1. Create a Table of [zPromo] Dups by [RecID]             (copied to [zEPromo200"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"10112])"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"DeleteObject"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     Delete [zPromoDupsT]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zPromoDupsT"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"CopyObject"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     Recreate [zPromoDupsT] from [zPromoDupsStruct]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:""
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zPromoDupsT"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zPromoDupsStruct"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     Populate [zPromoDupsT] via [zPromoDupsAQ] replacing [zPromoDupsMTQ] with an"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:" AQ, [zPromoDupsAQ]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     [zPromoDupsAQ]> [zPromoDupLeadQ]+[zPromo] yields table of records to be mar"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"ked for deletion"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zPromoDupsAQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"         Using a query [zPromoDupsQ] results in an un-updatable query"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     Mark [zPromo] Dups for Deletion"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"     [zPromoMarkDupsTUQ] replacing [zPromoMarkDupsUQ] UQ didn't like having an u"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"nderlying Q"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zPromoMarkDupsTUQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"          [zPromoDupsQ]> [zPromoDupLeadQ]+[zItemSub] yields records to be marked"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:" for deletion"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"          [zPromoDupLeadQ]> [zItemSub] Where Count > 1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"2. Delete Dups in  [zPromo]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zPromoKillDupsDQ]>  [zPromo]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zPromoKillDupsDQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"3. Use table [zPromoDupsT] to delete orphaned [zBuys]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    Mark [zBuy] Dups for Deletion via [zBuyMarkDupsTUQ]>[zPromoDupsT]+[zBuy]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zBuyMarkDupsTUQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    Delete [zBuy] Dups - [zBuyKillDupsDQ]>  [zBuy]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zBuyKillDupsDQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"4. Use table [zPromoDupsT] to delete orphaned [zItemSubs]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    Mark [zItemSub] Dups for Deletion via [zItemSubMarkDupsTUQ]>[zPromoDupsT]+[z"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"Buy]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zItemSubMarkDupsTUQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zItemSubKillDupsDQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"5. Kill duped ItemCodes in [zItemSub] - Good Promos but ItemCodes duped"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    Where there are no ItemCodes duped, within a Promo, by [RecID], the followin"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"g Qs have no effect."
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zItemSub]    (copied to [zEItemSub20010111])"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zItemSubDupsAQ]> [zItemSubDupLeadQ]+[zItemSub] yields table of records to b"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"e marked for deletion"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zItemSubDupsAQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"1"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"        [zItemSubDupLeadQ]> [zItemSub]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"OpenQuery"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"zItemSubKillSubDupsDQ"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"0"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"2KFLDTBL.mdb [zItemSub] copied as [zItemSub20100111] for testing"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zItemSub]= 2KFLDTBL.mdb [zEItemSub]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zPromo]= 2KFLDTBL.mdb [zEPromo]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zVendor]= 2KFLDTBL.mdb [zVendor]"

./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zItemSub].[Code]<>[zItemSubDupLeadQ].[CodeID]"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zItemSub].[RecID] Links 1to1 w/ [zItemSubDupLeadQ].[RecID] And"
./macros/DupsFixM.bas:"    [zItemSub].[HSICode] Links 1to1 w/ [zItemSubDupLeadQ].[HSICode]"

./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"rs later..."
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"@ 0:15 hrs (12:15 am) W:\\Vip_Dropoff\\update_vip_buffer.mdb VIP (Wayne Slingluf"
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"f) picks up the data and deletes the database."
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"Process Description -"
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"So, Promos.mdb has until midnight to pick up and process the VIP info, checking "
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"the [Promotion_Header_Update].[Done] flag for each completed import."
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"Wayne reads the database [Promotion_Header_Update].[Done] field and then deletes"
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:" those records from the next night's pending file."
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"Scheduler launchs [VIPimportAppM] the import append macro @ 21:00 hrs (9:00 pm),"
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:" then launches [VIPexportM] @ 21:30 hrs (9:30 pm)"
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"[VIPimportAppM] gets data, (Approved Headers, Details and Active Vendors), adds "
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"it to the master listings (in Promos.mdb), and then marks the records imported."
./macros/VIPexportQA.bas:"Then (a half hour later) the Scheduler launches this macro, [VIPexportM]"
